Defendant Anthony L Rosa in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  Defendant Anthony L Rosa in custody.  Jesica A Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 7 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 94 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 1/2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 4 1/2 YEARS.  The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program AFTER serving the first 18 months of this sentence.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take any and all prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety, no drugs or alcohol with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victim Ranjit S. or RM Petroleum located at 1801 W. Greenfield Ave.;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample if not previously submitted- pay surcharge;
*Pay all mandatory applicable surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 

The Court finds the state in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given.
